Reasoning: The paper discusses the computational complexity of video games and applies metatheorems to analyze several games. This falls under the scope of computational game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of common elements or mechanics in video games suggests a focus on algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The analysis of the complexity of video games also involves the study of computational complexity (cs.CC).
